  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Roll out shortcrust pastry to a thickness of 1/8 inch (3 mm).",
    "Cut into 4-6 equal pieces, depending on desired toast size.",
    "Place pastry pieces on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.",
    "Top each pastry piece with a spoonful of feta cheese, some olives, artichoke hearts, sun-dried tomatoes, and a sprinkle of parsley.",
    "Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with garlic, lemon zest, salt, and pepper.",
    "Bake for 15-20 minutes, or until pastry is golden brown and cheese is melted and slightly puffed.",
    "Remove from oven and let cool for a few minutes before serving.",
    "Serve warm, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
  ],
